# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TestHR database connection
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# LOCAL DEV (default): Prisma 7's built-in Postgres.
#   npx prisma dev --name testhr --detach
#   Then copy the printed prisma+postgres://... URL into DATABASE_URL in .env
#
# SUPABASE (production / shared):
#   1. Create a project at https://supabase.com (region: Canada Central — ca-central-1
#      — for Law 25 / PIPEDA data residency).
#   2. Project Settings → Database → Connection string → "Prisma".
#   3. Use the **pooled** connection (port 6543, ?pgbouncer=true) for DATABASE_URL,
#      and the **direct** connection (port 5432) for DIRECT_URL (used by migrations).
#
# IMPORTANT (Prisma 7 pg driver adapter): use the IPv4 **pooler** host
# (aws-<n>-<region>.pooler.supabase.com), NOT db.<ref>.supabase.co (IPv6-only).
# Add `uselibpqcompat=true` so pg treats sslmode=require as "encrypt" (libpq
# semantics) rather than verify-full. For strict verification, install Supabase's
# CA cert and use sslmode=verify-full.
#
# App runtime + migrations (session pooler, 5432):
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-<n>-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require&uselibpqcompat=true"
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-<n>-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require"
#
# Production serverless: switch DATABASE_URL to the transaction pooler (6543),
# keep DIRECT_URL on 5432 for migrations.

DATABASE_URL=
# DIRECT_URL=

# Anthropic API key for the HR Co-Pilot + agents (model: claude-opus-4-8).
# Leave blank / placeholder to use built-in canned responses; set a real
# "sk-ant-..." key to enable live Claude calls.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
